{"id": 4813, "title": "Ticket #4813: Infinite recursion with ClassAd eval() function", "description": "<blockquote>\nIn the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> library, it's possible to set up an infinite recursion during evaluation when using the <code>eval()</code> function in an expression.\n\n<p>With the following <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span>, evaluating attribute <code>A</code> or <code>B2</code> will overflow the stack.\n\n</p><p></p><div class=\"verbatim\">\n<pre>[\n  A = eval(\"A\");\n  B = \"eval(B)\";\n  B2 = eval(B);\n]\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>The <code>EvalState</code> object prevents infinite recursion when there's a loop in attribute references, by halting the evaluation when it has gone more than 1000 levels deep. We should do the same for <code>eval()</code> calls.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Jan-08 11:53:08 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW</strong>: Looks good!</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jan-08 11:59</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1b6bdcd6f260724515dc9d6b986577f6e04af59e\">[42142]</a></span>: Docs for <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> eval() infinite recursion bug fix. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4813\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4813'); return false;\" title=\"Infinite recursion with ClassAd eval() function\">#4813</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jan-08 11:08</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/325ef3b4519cfc984dfbc7cc0c61df3531c01d07\">[42139]</a></span>: Prevent infinite recursion with <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> eval() function. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4813\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4813'); return false;\" title=\"Infinite recursion with ClassAd eval() function\">#4813</a></span> If an attribute's value includes an eval() of that attribute's name, then we can end up with an infinite recursion on evaluation. Use the EvalState's depth limiter to prevent this.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2015-Jan-08 12:00", "status": "resolved", "created": "2015-Jan-08 10:06", "fixed_version": "2015-Jan-08 10:06", "broken_version": "v070501", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "ClassAd", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}